@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{elfeed-ai.el} adds AI-powered content curation to @uref{https://github.com/skeeto/elfeed, elfeed}, the Emacs @*
feed reader.  It solves the problem of information overload: rather @*
than manually scanning every entry in your feeds, you describe your @*
interests once in natural language, and @samp{elfeed-ai} continuously @*
evaluates new entries and surfaces only the content that matters to @*
you. @*

The package uses @uref{https://github.com/karthink/gptel, gptel} to send each entry's title and content to a @*
language model, which returns a relevance score between 0.0 and 1.0 @*
and, optionally, a brief summary.  If @code{elfeed-ai-relevance-threshold} @*
is set, entries scoring at or above the threshold are tagged (by @*
default with @code{elfeed-ai}), which you can use in elfeed's standard @*
search filter syntax to view only curated content. @*

@samp{elfeed-ai} integrates with elfeed through three mechanisms: @*

@itemize
@item
@strong{Automatic scoring} via @code{elfeed-new-entry-hook}.  When new entries @*
arrive during an elfeed update, they are queued and scored @*
asynchronously one at a time.  Each scored entry receives an AI @*
relevance score and a brief summary, stored as @code{elfeed-meta} @*
properties (@ref{Scoring entries}). @*

@item
@strong{Search buffer column}.  A custom @*
@code{elfeed-search-print-entry-function} adds a score column between the @*
date and title, with color-coded faces for high and low scores @*
(@ref{Faces}). @*

@item
@strong{Show buffer summary}.  After-advice on @code{elfeed-show-refresh} @*
injects the AI-generated summary above the original content, giving @*
you a quick overview before reading the full entry. @*
@end itemize

A daily budget system prevents runaway API costs.  The budget can @*
track either estimated tokens or actual dollar cost (the latter @*
requires @samp{gptel-plus}), and resets at a configurable hour each day @*
(@ref{Budget}). @*

The package also provides a @uref{https://github.com/magit/transient, transient} menu for interactive adjustment @*
of all settings (@ref{Transient menu}). @*

Dependencies: @samp{elfeed} (3.4.1+), @samp{gptel} (0.9+), @samp{transient} (0.7+), @*
Emacs 29.1 or later. @*

