@node Quick start
@section Quick start

@lisp
(require 'elfeed-ai)

(setq elfeed-ai-interest-profile
      "AI safety, Emacs, functional programming, philosophy of mind,
       effective altruism, longevity research")

(elfeed-ai-mode 1)
@end lisp

New entries are scored automatically when elfeed fetches them.  Scores @*
are stored as entry metadata, so you can sort the search buffer by @*
relevance. @*

To also filter by relevance, set @code{elfeed-ai-relevance-threshold} to a @*
value between 0.0 and 1.0 (e.g., @code{0.5}).  Entries scoring at or above @*
the threshold are tagged with @code{elfeed-ai-score-tag} (default @*
@code{elfeed-ai}), which you can use in elfeed search filters: @*

@example
+elfeed-ai +unread
@end example

You can also point @code{elfeed-ai-interest-profile} at a file containing a @*
longer profile (@ref{Interest profile}).  To score entries that arrived @*
before you enabled the mode, use @samp{M-x elfeed-ai-score-unscored} @*
(@ref{Scoring unscored entries}). @*

