@node Enabling the mode
@section Enabling the mode

@findex elfeed-ai-mode
The command @code{elfeed-ai-mode} is a global minor mode that activates all @*
@samp{elfeed-ai} integrations.  When enabled, it: @*

@itemize
@item
Sets @code{elfeed-search-print-entry-function} to a custom function that @*
displays the AI score column (@ref{Search buffer display}). @*
@item
Installs @code{elfeed-ai-sort} as @code{elfeed-search-sort-function} if @*
@code{elfeed-ai-sort-by-score} is non-nil (@ref{Display}). @*
@item
Adds @code{elfeed-ai--enqueue} to @code{elfeed-new-entry-hook} if @*
@code{elfeed-ai-auto-score} is non-nil (@ref{Scoring behavior}). @*
@item
Advises @code{elfeed-show-refresh} to inject AI summaries. @*
@item
If @samp{elfeed-tube} is available, advises @code{elfeed-tube-show} to @*
re-inject the AI summary after elfeed-tube modifies the show buffer @*
(@ref{elfeed-tube integration}). @*
@end itemize

When disabled, all integrations are cleanly removed and the original @*
print and sort functions are restored.  The pending scoring queue is @*
also cleared. @*

@node Scoring entries
@section Scoring entries

@findex elfeed-ai-score
The command @code{elfeed-ai-score} is a context-sensitive command for @*
scoring entries.  Its behavior depends on the current buffer: @*

@itemize
@item
In the @strong{show buffer}, it scores the displayed entry.  If the entry @*
has already been scored, it signals an error unless called with a @*
prefix argument (@samp{C-u}), which forces a re-score.  After scoring, it @*
refreshes the show buffer to display the new summary. @*

@item
In the @strong{search buffer}, it queues all selected entries (or the entry @*
at point when no region is active) for scoring.  Already-scored @*
entries are skipped unless called with a prefix argument. @*
@end itemize

In both cases, the command reports how many entries were queued and how @*
many were already scored.  Scoring proceeds asynchronously in the @*
background; a message is displayed in the echo area when the batch @*
completes, along with the total cost if dollar tracking is available. @*

@node Scoring unscored entries
@section Scoring unscored entries

@findex elfeed-ai-score-unscored
The command @code{elfeed-ai-score-unscored} walks the entire elfeed @*
database and queues all entries from the last N days that have not yet @*
been scored.  By default, N is the value of @*
@code{elfeed-ai-score-unscored-days} (@ref{Scoring behavior}).  With a prefix @*
argument (@samp{C-u}), the command prompts for a custom number of days. @*

This is useful when you first enable @samp{elfeed-ai} on an existing elfeed @*
database, or after changing your interest profile and wanting to @*
re-evaluate recent entries. @*

@node Checking budget status
@section Checking budget status

@findex elfeed-ai-budget-status
The command @code{elfeed-ai-budget-status} displays the current daily usage @*
in the echo area.  In @code{tokens} mode, it shows tokens used versus the @*
limit.  In @code{dollars} mode, it shows the dollar amount used versus the @*
limit.  Both modes show the remaining budget. @*

@node Toggling sort order
@section Toggling sort order

@findex elfeed-ai-toggle-sort
The command @code{elfeed-ai-toggle-sort} switches between sorting the @*
search buffer by AI score (highest first) and the original sort order @*
(typically by date).  When score sorting is enabled, @*
@code{elfeed-search-sort-function} is set to @code{elfeed-ai-sort} @*
(@ref{Sorting}); when disabled, the function saved before @samp{elfeed-ai} @*
modified it is restored. @*

The search buffer is refreshed immediately after toggling.  This @*
command is also available in the transient menu (@ref{Transient menu}). @*

