@node Scoring
@section Scoring

@findex elfeed-ai-score-entry
The function @code{elfeed-ai-score-entry} is the core scoring function.  It @*
takes an elfeed ENTRY and a CALLBACK, sends the entry to the @*
configured AI backend via @code{gptel-request}, and calls CALLBACK with a @*
@code{(score . summary)} cons cell on success or @code{nil} on failure. @*

Before making the API call, the function checks three preconditions: @*
the interest profile must be non-empty, the daily budget must not be @*
exhausted, and the entry must have at least a title or content.  If @*
any check fails, CALLBACK is called with @code{nil} immediately. @*

The function constructs a system message containing the interest @*
profile and scoring instructions, and a user message containing the @*
entry's title, author, and truncated content.  The system message is @*
marked for prompt caching via @code{gptel-use-cache}, so that repeated @*
scoring requests reuse the cached system prompt. @*

On receiving a response, the function parses the JSON, records token @*
and cost usage (@ref{Budget}), stores the score and summary as @*
@code{elfeed-meta} properties on the entry, and, if @*
@code{elfeed-ai-relevance-threshold} is non-nil, applies or removes the @*
relevance tag (@ref{Scoring behavior}). @*

@findex elfeed-ai-budget-exhausted-p
The function @code{elfeed-ai-budget-exhausted-p} returns non-nil if today's @*
budget is exhausted.  This is useful in custom hooks or conditions @*
where you want to check whether scoring will proceed before queuing @*
entries. @*

@node Search buffer display
@section Search buffer display

@findex elfeed-ai-search-print-entry
The function @code{elfeed-ai-search-print-entry} is the custom @*
@code{elfeed-search-print-entry-function} installed by @code{elfeed-ai-mode}. @*
It renders each entry with the standard date, title, feed, and tags @*
columns, plus an additional score column between the date and title. @*

The score column is 6 characters wide.  Scored entries display their @*
score as a four-character float (e.g., @samp{0.85}); unscored entries @*
display =  - =.  The score is propertized with one of three faces @*
depending on the thresholds (@ref{Display}): @*

@itemize
@item
@code{elfeed-ai-score-high-face} for scores at or above @*
@code{elfeed-ai-score-high-threshold}. @*
@item
@code{elfeed-ai-score-low-face} for scores at or below @*
@code{elfeed-ai-score-low-threshold}. @*
@item
@code{elfeed-ai-score-face} for scores in between, or for unscored @*
entries. @*
@end itemize

@node Sorting
@section Sorting

@findex elfeed-ai-sort
The function @code{elfeed-ai-sort} is the sort predicate installed as @*
@code{elfeed-search-sort-function} when score sorting is active.  It sorts @*
entries by descending AI score, with unscored entries (which have no @*
@code{:ai-score} metadata) placed after all scored entries.  Entries with @*
equal scores are sorted by date (newest first). @*

Internally, unscored entries are assigned a sentinel value of @code{-1.0}, @*
which is below the valid score range of 0.0--1.0, ensuring they @*
always appear last. @*

@node Faces
@chapter Faces

@samp{elfeed-ai} defines four faces for visual presentation of AI data: @*

@itemize
@item
@code{elfeed-ai-score-face} --- the default face for mid-range AI scores @*
in the search buffer.  Inherits from @code{shadow}.  Applied to scores @*
between @code{elfeed-ai-score-low-threshold} and @*
@code{elfeed-ai-score-high-threshold}, and to unscored entries. @*

@item
@code{elfeed-ai-score-high-face} --- face for high AI scores in the @*
search buffer.  Inherits from @code{success} with bold weight.  Applied @*
to scores at or above @code{elfeed-ai-score-high-threshold} (default @*
@code{0.7}). @*

@item
@code{elfeed-ai-score-low-face} --- face for low AI scores in the search @*
buffer.  Inherits from @code{shadow}.  Applied to scores at or below @*
@code{elfeed-ai-score-low-threshold} (default @code{0.3}). @*

@item
@code{elfeed-ai-summary-heading-face} --- face for the ``AI Summary'' @*
heading in the show buffer.  Inherits from @code{font-lock-keyword-face} @*
with bold weight. @*
@end itemize

You can customize these faces with @samp{M-x customize-face} or by setting @*
them in your init file.  The score thresholds that determine which @*
face is used are controlled by @code{elfeed-ai-score-high-threshold} and @*
@code{elfeed-ai-score-low-threshold} (@ref{Display}). @*

@node Transient menu
@chapter Transient menu

@findex elfeed-ai-menu
The command @code{elfeed-ai-menu} opens a @uref{https://github.com/magit/transient, transient} menu providing @*
centralized access to all @samp{elfeed-ai} commands and settings.  The menu @*
is organized into four groups: @*

@itemize
@item
@strong{Score}: commands for scoring the current entry or selection @*
(@code{elfeed-ai-score}, bound to @samp{s}) and for scoring unscored entries @*
(@code{elfeed-ai-score-unscored}, bound to @samp{S}). @*

@item
@strong{Display}: toggles for sort order (@code{elfeed-ai-toggle-sort}, bound to @*
@samp{t}) and the minor mode (@code{elfeed-ai-mode}, bound to @samp{m}). @*

@item
@strong{Scoring}: interactive adjustment of the AI model (@samp{-m}), @*
auto-scoring (@samp{-a}), summary generation (@samp{-s}), relevance threshold @*
(@samp{-r}), max content length (@samp{-l}), and the number of days for @*
@code{elfeed-ai-score-unscored} (@samp{-d}). @*

@item
@strong{Budget}: toggle between token and dollar budget types (@samp{-t}), and @*
set the budget limit (@samp{-b}).  In dollar mode, the group heading @*
displays the total cost of the last 100 scored entries, helping you @*
calibrate the daily limit. @*
@end itemize

Changes made through the transient menu take effect immediately but @*
are not persisted across sessions.  To make them permanent, set the @*
corresponding user options in your init file. @*

You might bind the menu to a convenient key in elfeed: @*

@lisp
(define-key elfeed-search-mode-map (kbd "Y") #'elfeed-ai-menu)
(define-key elfeed-show-mode-map (kbd "Y") #'elfeed-ai-menu)
@end lisp

@node elfeed-tube integration
@chapter elfeed-tube integration

If you use @uref{https://github.com/karthink/elfeed-tube, elfeed-tube} alongside @samp{elfeed-ai}, the two packages @*
interact in the show buffer.  The issue is that @code{elfeed-tube-show} @*
replaces or modifies the show buffer content after @*
@code{elfeed-show-refresh} has already run, which would normally remove the @*
injected AI summary. @*

@samp{elfeed-ai} handles this automatically.  When @code{elfeed-ai-mode} is @*
enabled, it advises @code{elfeed-tube-show} so that the AI summary is @*
re-injected after elfeed-tube finishes its modifications.  This advice @*
is installed eagerly if @samp{elfeed-tube} is already loaded, or deferred @*
via @code{with-eval-after-load} if it has not yet been loaded. @*

No configuration is required on your part: if both packages are @*
installed and their respective modes are active, the integration works @*
transparently. @*

